condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A., Para 4(a) | Description :The Project Secretariat shall recruit one FinancialManagement Consultant within one month after effectiveness. | Due Date :04-Sep-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A., Para 4(b) | Description :The Project Secretariat shall recruit one ProcurementConsultant within one month after effectiveness. | Due Date :04-Sep-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A., Para 5 | Description :The Project Secretariat shall submit to the Bank every sixmonths, a draft semi-annual training and workshops plan identifying activities and beneficiaries and proposed expenditures. |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.A., Para 1 | Description :The Project Secretariat shall submit to the Bank every calendarquarter a quarterly progress report. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.B., Para 2 | Description :The Project Secretariat shall submit to the Bank every calendarquarter a quarterly financial management report. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.B., Para 3 | Description :The Project Secretariat shall submit to the Bank not later thansix months after the end of the Country's Fiscal Year, a project-account audit report. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section I. A. 3 (c) | Description :Update the Project Implementation Manual and the Financial Management Manual,in a manner satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :15-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Section I. C. 3 | Description :The Recipient shall collect, compile and submit to the Association consolidatedreports on the status of compliance with the Environmental and Social Safeguards Activities Document, giving details of: (a)measures taken in accordance with the said instruments; (b) conditions, if any, which interfere or threaten to interfere with theimplementation of the said measures; and (c) remedial measures ta | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Section II. A. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepareProject Reports in accordance with the provisions of Section 4.08 of the General Conditions [of the Financing Agreement] and on thebasis of indicators agreed with the Association and set out in the Project Implementation Manual. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Section II. B. 2 | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association as part of theProject Report, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter, in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section II. B. 3 | Description :The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited in accordance with theprovisions of Section 4.09(b) of the General Conditions. Each audit of the Financial Statements shall cover the period of one (1)fiscal year of the Recipient. | Frequency :Yearly
